content:
Can you use the following Latex equation to calculate the shipping cost for a 10-pound package traveling from New York City to Chicago?
\begin{equation}
Shipping Cost = (Distance \cdot Rate) + Additional Fees + Taxes
\end{equation}
Assume the distance between the two cities is 800 miles and the standard shipping rate is $0.50 per mile. Additional fees are $5 and taxes are 8%. Show your work and round the final cost to two decimal places. Good luck with the puzzle!
